[anchor=cache][b]Changing The Location Of Your Cache (not url)[/b][/anchor]
[B]Classes Modified:[/B] signlink.java
[B]Difficulty:[/B] 2/10

instead of loading your cache by useing the moparscape cache why not use your own
(moparscape cache directory)
[code]C:/windows/.mpr_file_store_32/[/code]

to change the location it takes place in
[code]private static String findcachedir()[/code]

in their youll see
[code]return "somethinghere";[/code]

the
<blockquote>[b]somethinghere[/b]</blockquote>
will be the location to your cache for example
[code]C:/Documents and Settings/username/Desktop/[/code]
that would load your cache from your desktop on the c drive

you could also have
[code]foldername/[/code]
that will locate the cache folder inside of your client folder

make sure that all \ are made into /

[code]c:\src\cache\[/code]
will not work

[code]c:/src/cache/[/code]
will work


